s","Psammoma bodies","Reed-Sternberg cells","Foam cells"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPhaeochromocytomas are neuroendocrine tumours arising from chromaffin cells of the adrenal medulla. The characteristic histological features include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESustentacular cells\u003C/strong\u003E which provide structural support to the chromaffin cells and can be highlighted by S100 protein immunostaining\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EChromaffin cells arranged in nests (zellballen pattern)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAbundant cytoplasm with fine granules\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect as:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColloid-filled follicles\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of thyroid tissue\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsammoma bodies\u003C/strong\u003E are seen in papillary thyroid carcinoma and meningiomas\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReed-Sternberg cells\u003C/strong\u003E are diagnostic of Hodgkin lymphoma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFoam cells\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of atherosclerotic plaques\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of sustentacular cells in a characteristic zellballen arrangement is a key diagnostic feature of phaeochromocytoma on microscopy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Phaeochromocytomas contain characteristic sustentacular cells that provide structural support to chromaffin cells.","Phaeochromocytomas are composed of chromaffin cells arranged in nests or \u0027zellballen\u0027 pattern.","Sustentacular cells can be identified by S100 protein immunostaining."],"references":["Patel T, Singleton LA, Mejia M, Senior A, Millis RM. Pheochromocytoma: A Troublesome Tumor. Cureus. 2023 Sep 18;15(9):e45490. doi: 10.7759/cureus.45490. PMID: 37727845; PMCID: PMC10506759.","Clark, O. H., D